<title>INDIA: FII holdings in 14 Indian firms hit 24 pct ceiling.</title>
<headline>FII holdings in 14 Indian firms hit 24 pct ceiling.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-03-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Foreign institutional investors' (FII) holdings have reached the 24 percent ceiling in 14 Indian firms, the central bank said on Saturday.  </p>
<p>The firms are: Salora International Ltd, Maral Overseas Ltd, Modiluft Ltd, Zee Telefilms Ltd, Infosys Technologies Ltd, Unitech Ltd, Mastek Ltd, Housing Development Finance Corporation Ltd, Satyam Computers Services Ltd, Jaiparabolic Springs Ltd, Polyplex Corporation Ltd, Nagarjuna Construction Ltd, Patheja Forgings Auto Parts Manufacturing Ltd and Shivalik Projects Ltd.</p>
<p>The 1997/98 budget (April-March) unveiled on February 28 proposed to raise the FII ceiling to 30 percent from 24 percent, but this will become effective only after the proposal is accepted by parliament, a Reserve Bank of India official said.</p>
